  Translator: Andrew Harvey
By: Rumi
Format: verse
Title: I Lost My World
---
I lost my world, my fame, my mind --
The Sun appeared, and all the shadows ran.
I ran after them, but vanished as I ran --
Light ran after me and hunted me down.
